---
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro"
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro"
---

<PageLayout
  titleTag="CV | Eder Christian"
  title="CV"
  description="The career timeline of Eder Christian, frontend engineer."
>
  <div class="container cv">
    <PageHeader title="CV" subtitle="Software Engineer. Remote Contractor. Self-Taught Builder." />

    <h2>2026</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Rebuilt this site from scratch, added a <a href="/garden">Garden</a> section
        as a public second brain for notes in progress.
      </li>
      <li>
        Spent a week in the US — mostly in Minneapolis, MN for an in-person AI Engineering
        workshop with Scott Moss (Netflix) at <a
          href="https://frontendmasters.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">Frontend Masters</a
        > HQ, plus a few days in Orlando, FL.
      </li>
      <li>
        Shipped the MVP of <a
          href="https://perspion.whey.dev"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">Perspion</a
        >, YouTube comment intelligence for creators. Turns viewer comments into
        content radar, sentiment maps, and question banks. First product under
        WheyDev, the one-engineer studio I run as a side project in my free time.
      </li>
      <li>
        Joined Google Developer Group Londrina as an organizer, helping run the
        monthly in-person events and writing for the GDG newsletter on Substack.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2025</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Served as a judge in an <a
          href="https://devsdeimpacto.imasters.com.br/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">online hackathon</a
        > focused on AI solutions for climate, education, and public services.
      </li>
      <li>
        Spent a week in New York attending frontend, UX, and design
        events — including a visit to Figma's office and a local meetup.
      </li>
      <li>
        Started transitioning into a Product Engineer role — combining frontend,
        data, and user-facing impact.
      </li>
      <li>
        Created a <a
          href="https://youtube.com/@ederchristian"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">YouTube channel</a
        >
        in English focused on dev life, personal systems, and stories that shaped me.
      </li>
      <li>
        At Automatiq:
        <ul>
          <li>Led the implementation of Dark Mode across multiple views.</li>
          <li>
            Designed and shipped a feature for order drafts — reduced friction and
            improved publishing workflows.
          </li>
          <li>
            Enhanced performance and usability of complex views (like Events and
            Consigned Inventory), improving clarity and speed.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Started deepening CS fundamentals and exploring AI workflows</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2024</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        At Automatiq:
        <ul>
          <li>Delivered high-impact features for high-volume B2B users.</li>
          <li>
            Simplified admin tools (API key manager, advanced filtering) for
            better DX and decision-making.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Spent a month in Silicon Valley attending AI events, connecting with
        founders, and visiting startups and major tech companies (including
        FAANG).
      </li>
      <li>
        Launched a small-scale course (in Portuguese) on AI-powered productivity —
        combining developer mindset with real systems.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2023</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        At Automatiq:
        <ul>
          <li>
            Redesigned and shipped user-friendly admin tools for order management
            and ticket mapping.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Discovered late-diagnosed autism (Asperger, Level 1), leading to refined
        systems for focus and deep work.
      </li>
      <li>
        Developed minimalist routines to manage energy and clarity, applied daily
        to remote dev life.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2022</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Taught English online through a nonprofit organization.</li>
      <li>
        Completed 500+ hours of <a
          href="https://cambly.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">Cambly</a
        > tutoring and reached English fluency.
      </li>
      <li>
        Joined <a
          href="https://automatiq.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">Automatiq</a
        > — a U.S.-based company in New York that builds automation tools for the
        secondary ticket market.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2020-2021</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Became a partner at StartSe after years of contribution across tech,
        design, and operations.
      </li>
      <li>
        Helped develop a custom online events platform that doubled the company's
        revenue compared to in-person events from the previous year.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2019</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Contributed to building StartSe's main student platform and helped
        redesign the company's news portal.
      </li>
      <li>
        Transitioned from basic HTML/CSS work to building interfaces with
        JavaScript frameworks.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2018</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Visited Silicon Valley for the first time — spent two weeks in California,
        including one week in a startup immersion program called Learning
        Experience.
      </li>
      <li>
        Built hundreds of landing pages for events and online courses at StartSe.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2017</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Started learning English from scratch using online tutoring platforms like
        Cambly.
      </li>
      <li>
        Moved to São Paulo with R$700 (~US$200) and no place to stay — accepted a
        junior dev position at <a
          href="https://startse.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">StartSe</a
        >, an education startup in Brazil.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2012-2016</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Worked in tech support and briefly at a marketing agency before pivoting
        to dev.
      </li>
      <li>
        Completed a postgraduate program in Web Application Development (little
        practical impact).
      </li>
      <li>Studied Information Technology Management at a public college.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .cv {
    padding-top: 64px;
    padding-bottom: 32px;
    font-size: var(--fs-body);
    line-height: var(--lh-base);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .cv h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: var(--fs-eyebrow);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 32px 0 12px;
  }
  .cv ul {
    padding-left: 1.3em;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }
  .cv ul ul {
    margin-top: 6px;
  }
  .cv li {
    margin: 6px 0;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .cv a {
    color: var(--accent);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 213, 159, 0.35);
  }
  .cv a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--accent);
  }
</style>
